==History==
Founded in 1975 by Roger V. Ohanesian, Harvard Eye Associates is involved with a number of charity works.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://armenianow.com/features/6895/check_up_health_care_still_in_tran |title=Check Up: Health care still in transition in independent Armenia - Features |publisher=ArmeniaNow.com |date= |accessdate=2011-12-12}}</ref> The [[Armenian Eye Care Project]], an international charity that donates medicine, treatment and surgery to [[Armenia]], was founded by Ohanesian in 1992.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.reporter.am/index.cfm?furl=/go/article/2008-10-18-new-medical-clinics-equipment-in-coaf-villages-go-hand-and-hand-with-professional-public-health-training&view=displaypageArticlePrint |title=New medical clinics, equipment in COAF villages go hand-and-hand with professional, public health training |publisher=Reporter.am |date=2008-10-18 |accessdate=2011-12-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Avakian |first=Florence |url=http://www.armenianweekly.com/2009/12/02/aahpo-fundraiser-at-ny-stock-exchange-benefits-eyecare-project-voskevan-clinic/ |title=AAHPO Fundraiser at NY Stock Exchange Benefits Eyecare Project, Voskevan Clinic |publisher=Armenian Weekly |date=2009-12-02 |accessdate=2011-12-12}}</ref> Dr. Ohanesian and his colleagues have traveled to all parts of Armenia, from earthquake epicenters to war zones, performing reconstructive surgery on hundreds of victims of natural disasters, warfare and landmines.<ref>http://www.eyecareproject.com/about-aecp/5-point-program/direct-patient-care</ref> Dr. Ohanesian has completed over 50,000 surgical eye procedures and shares his expertise with other eye doctors as a diagnostic and surgical consultant.<ref>http://www.harvardeye.com/about/roger-ohanesian.html</ref> Harvard Eye Associates also offers charity services at home, including free [[Pterygium (conjunctiva)|pterygium]] screenings and health fairs.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ocregister.com/news/lot-302137-pterygium-screenings.html |title=Free screenings coming for 'surfer's eye' |publisher=The Orange County Register |date=2011-05-26 |first=Fred |last=Swegles |accessdate=2011-12-12}}</ref> Harvard Eye Associates is one of the most experienced pterygium surgery practices in the world, and Dr. John A. Hovanesian of this practice recently published a book on his advanced surgery technique.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.slackbooks.com/pterygium |title=Pterygium: Techniques and Technologies for Surgical Success |publisher=Slackbooks.com |date=2008-05-19 |accessdate=2011-12-12}}</ref>{{Clarify|date=December 2011}}

Many physicians at Harvard Eye Associates perform presentations at OD continuing education seminars and patient information seminars.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.osnhawaiianeye.com/faculty.asp |title=Hawaiian Eye 2012 &#124; Faculty |publisher=Osnhawaiianeye.com |date=2011-12-30 |accessdate=2011-12-30}}</ref>{{Clarify|date=December 2011}} Dr. Ohanesian is an acknowledged leader in eye surgery and presently teaches medical and surgical techniques in the United States and internationally.<ref>http://www.aao.org/publications/eyenet/200811/international.cfm</ref> He teaches about the new advanced high-tech lens implants of Bausch and Lomb Crystalens®,<ref>http://www.oteurope.com/ophthalmologytimeseurope/author/authorInfo.jsp?id=42901</ref> Allergan Tecnis® Multifocal and Alcon ReSTOR® lenses.<ref>http://www.slackbooks.com/masteringIOLs</ref>

